To determine the return on equity, let us compute the total equity at year-end:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Equity}&=\text{Beg. Equity}+\text{Net Income}-\text{Dividends}\\[12pt]
&={\$145,000}+{\$27,000}-{\$5,800}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$166,200}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The total equity that will be used to compute the return on equity amounts to \$166,200.**

To determine the sustainable growth rate, let us first compute the return on equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Return on Equity}&=\frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Total Equity}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$27,000}{\$166,200}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.1625}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The return on equity is 0.1625.**

Now, let us compute the retained earnings:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retained Earnings}&=\text{Net Income}-\text{Dividend}\\[12pt]
&={\$27,000}-{\$5,800}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$21,200}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retained earnings is \$21,200.**

Now, let us compute the retention ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retention Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Retained Earnings}}{\text{Net Income}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$21,200}{\$27,000}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.79}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{79\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retention ratio is 79\%.**

To determine the sustainable growth rate, let us first compute the return on equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Return on Equity}&=\frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Beginning Equity}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$27,000}{\$145,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.1862}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The return on equity is 0.1862.**

Using the beginning equity, the formula to determine the sustainable growth rate will be modified as follows. Now, let us compute the sustainable growth rate:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Sustainable Growth Rate}&=\text{Return on Equity}\times\text{Retention Ratio}\times 100\\[12pt]
&={0.1862\times 79\%}\times 100\\[12pt]
&={0.1471}\times 100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{14.71\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The sustainable growth rate of the company using the beginning equity is 14.71\%.**
